      <hedline>
        <hl1>Gentleman Johnny</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Harris Green letter on Jamie Malanowski's July 2 article on dearth of Revolutionary War movies notes Burt Lancaster and Kirk Douglas starred with Laurence Olivier in 1959 version of Devil's Disciple (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Jamie Malanowski writes, ''Burt Lancaster, Kirk Douglas, Gregory Peck -- any of them would have done a good job besting the libertine General Johnny Burgoyne (Laurence Harvey, maybe, or Dirk Bogarde) at Saratoga. . . .'' [''The Revolutionary War Is Lost on Hollywood,'' July 2]. In fact, Lancaster and Douglas did confront Gentleman Johnny, unimprovably acted by Laurence Olivier, in the 1959 try at Shaw's ''Devil's Disciple.''</p>
        <p>HARRIS GREEN  Manhattan</p>
      </block>
